        <div class="slide bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-100 via-indigo-50 to-blue-100 p-12 lg:p-16 flex flex-col justify-center items-center text-center">
            <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-6xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Project: Virtual Lecter</h1>
            <p class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-light text-indigo-700">A Clinician-First VR Platform for Stress Regulation and Performance.</p>
            <div class="absolute bottom-10 text-indigo-600 text-lg">[Your Team Name/Logo]</div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 2: The Problem -->
        <div class="slide bg-white p-12 lg:p-16 flex flex-col justify-center">
            <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-red-600 mb-8">The Problem: The High-Stakes Exam</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-4 text-xl lg:text-2xl text-slate-700 ml-6">
                <li><strong class="text-red-600">Acute Exam Anxiety:</strong> Students experience panic, cognitive blanking, and dissociation.</li>
                <li><strong class="text-red-600">The Neurodivergent Gap:</strong> Standard tools fail students with ADHD, whose working memory is a key vulnerability.</li>
                <li><strong class="text-red-600">The Access Crisis:</strong> A critical shortage of mental health support, with only <strong class="text-red-700 font-semibold">0.3 psychologists per 100,000 people</strong>.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-8 text-xl lg:text-2xl font-semibold bg-red-50 border border-red-200 p-4 rounded-lg text-red-800">
                The result: Students are left to manage overwhelming stress alone, right when they need to perform their best.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 3: The Challenge & Insight -->
        <div class="slide bg-white p-12 lg:p-16 flex flex-col justify-center">
            <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-cyan-600 mb-6">The Challenge & Our Clinical Insight</h2>
            
            <div class="bg-slate-100 border border-slate-200 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-500">The Hackathon Challenge:</h3>
                <p class="text-lg text-slate-700">"Develop a VR experience... [using] any one instance of exposure therapy... Describe the use-case scenario in detail..."</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-cyan-50 border border-cyan-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-cyan-700">Our Clinical Insight:</h3>
                <p class="text-xl lg:text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Exposure without regulation is re-traumatizing.</p>
                <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 mb-4">Effective therapy requires a "bottom-up" approach:</p>
                <ol class="list-decimal list-outside ml-6 text-xl lg:text-2xl space-y-2 font-medium">
                    <li><span class="bg-cyan-500 text-white rounded px-2 py-1">First:</span> Regulate the body (Physiology).</li>
                    <li><span class="bg-cyan-400 text-white rounded px-2 py-1">Then:</span> Equip the mind (Skills).</li>
                    <li><span class="bg-cyan-300 text-gray-900 rounded px-2 py-1">Finally:</span> Face the challenge (Exposure).</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Slide 4: Our Solution -->
        <div class="slide bg-white p-12 lg:p-16 flex flex-col justify-center">
            <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-green-600 mb-8">Our Solution: A Hybrid Clinical Tool</h2>
            <p class="text-xl lg:text-2xl text-slate-700 mb-6">We are developing a <strong class="text-slate-900">therapist-facilitated VR platform</strong> that bridges the gap between clinic and home.</p>
            <p class="text-xl lg:text-2xl text-slate-600 italic mb-8">It's not a replacement for therapy; it's a <strong class="text-green-700 font-semibold not-italic">"therapeutic adjunct"</strong> that empowers clients with in-the-moment skills.</p>
            
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-lg">
                <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2">For the Client:</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-700">An on-demand "mental warm-up" and "panic toolkit."</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2">For the Therapist:</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-700">A scalable tool to assign, monitor, and guide treatment between sessions.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 5: The Use Case -->
        <div class="slide bg-white p-12 lg:p-16 flex flex-col justify-center">
            <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-amber-600 mb-8">The Use Case: From Panic to Performance</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-xl lg:text-2xl">
                <p><strong class="w-48 inline-block text-amber-700">1. The Environment:</strong> An Indoor <strong class="text-slate-900">"High-Stress Exam Hall"</strong></p>
                
                <p><strong class="w-48 inline-block text-amber-700">2. The Persona:</strong> <strong class="text-slate-900">"Chaithanya"</strong></p>
                <ul class="list-none list-outside ml-10 pl-4 border-l-2 border-amber-400 space-y-2 text-lg lg:text-xl">
                    <li><strong class="text-amber-700">Who:</strong> 15-year-old, diagnosed with ADHD & GAD.</li>
                    <li><strong class="text-amber-700">Problem:</strong> Experiences panic attacks, leading to "mind blank" dissociation.</li>
                    <li><strong class="text-amber-700">Goal:</strong> To *manage* stress, not eliminate it, to access his knowledge.</li>
                </ul>
                
                <p><strong class="w-48 inline-block text-amber-700">3. The Journey:</strong></p>
                <div class="flex items-center space-x-4 ml-10 text-lg lg:text-xl font-medium">
                    <span class="bg-red-500 text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Panic (Stress 8/10)</span>
                    <span class="text-amber-500 text-2xl">&rarr;</span>
                    <span class="bg-green-500 text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Manageable Nerves (Stress 4/10)</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 6: Part 1: The Demo -->
        <div class="slide bg-white p-12 lg:p-16 flex flex-col justify-center">
            <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-indigo-600 mb-6">Part 1: The Demo (Skills & Regulation)</h2>
            <p class="text-xl lg:text-2xl text-slate-700 mb-6">What you are about to see is the <strong class="text-slate-900">essential foundation</strong> of our platform.</p>
            <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-6">Before we can expose Chaithanya to an exam, we must give him the tools to self-regulate. Our prototype demonstrates these first two critical phases:</p>
            
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-3 text-xl lg:text-2xl text-slate-700 ml-6">
                <li><strong class="text-indigo-700">Phase 0: Triage & Rapport:</strong> Assess immediate stress.</li>
                <li><strong class="text-indigo-700">Phase 1: Grounding First:</strong> The 5-4-3-2-1 technique to pull him out of dissociation.</li>
                <li><strong class="text-indigo-700">Phase 2: ADHD-Adapted Breathing:</strong> A breathing exercise with *proprioceptive anchors* (finger tapping) to keep his brain engaged.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Slide 7: Live Demo -->
        <div class="slide bg-white p-12 lg:p-16 flex flex-col justify-center items-center">
