        <!-- Slide 8: Part 2: The Exposure (Full Vision) -->
        <div class="slide bg-white p-12 lg:p-16 flex flex-col justify-center">
            <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-purple-600 mb-6">Part 2: The Exposure (The Full Vision)</h2>
            <p class="text-xl lg:text-2xl text-slate-700 mb-6">The demo showed the <strong class="text-slate-900">safety tools</strong>. The next step is to build the <strong class="text-slate-900">core exposure therapy</strong>.</p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-lg">
                <div class="bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-purple-700 mb-2">Phase 4: Gradual Exposure Hierarchy</h3>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 space-y-2 text-slate-700">
                        <li>User starts at Level 1 (e.g., empty classroom).</li>
                        <li>They use the breathing tools from the demo to manage anxiety.</li>
                        <li>Once stress drops, they "level up" to a harder scene (e.g., full exam hall).</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-purple-700 mb-2">Phase 5: Peak Moment Protocol</h3>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 space-y-2 text-slate-700">
                        <li>Simulate specific triggers: A timer ticks down, an avatar asks a question.</li>
                        <li>User's goal is to use the grounding tools to stay present and avoid a "blank out."</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 9: The Clinical Workflow -->
        <div class="slide bg-white p-12 lg:p-16 flex flex-col justify-center">
            <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-teal-600 mb-8">The Clinical Workflow (Deployment)</h2>
            <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-6">This is how our platform integrates directly into a clinic:</p>
            <ol class="relative border-l border-teal-300 space-y-6">
                <li class="ml-6">
                    <span class="absolute flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6 bg-teal-500 rounded-full -left-3 ring-8 ring-white text-white font-bold">1</span>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-1">Assess & Personalize (In-Clinic)</h3>
                    <p class="text-base text-slate-600">Therapist conducts intake and enters client data (triggers, crisis plan, preferred voice) into our system.</p>
                </li>
                <li class="ml-6">
                    <span class="absolute flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6 bg-teal-500 rounded-full -left-3 ring-8 ring-white text-white font-bold">2</span>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-1">Supervised Practice (In-Clinic)</h3>
                    <p class="text-base text-slate-600">Client's first VR session is done *with the therapist present* to build confidence and ensure safety.</p>
                </li>
                <li class="ml-6">
                    <span class="absolute flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6 bg-teal-500 rounded-full -left-3 ring-8 ring-white text-white font-bold">3</span>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-1">Home Use (Client-Led)</h3>
                    <p class="text-base text-slate-600">Client uses the app at home as "homework" or as an "in-the-moment" tool before a real exam.</p>
                </li>
                <li class="ml-6">
                    <span class="absolute flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6 bg-teal-500 rounded-full -left-3 ring-8 ring-white text-white font-bold">4</span>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-1">Data Review (In-Clinic)</h3>
                    <p class="text-base text-slate-600">Therapist reviews data (stress scores, modules completed) on a dashboard to adjust the treatment plan.</p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Slide 10: Unique Value Proposition -->
        <div class="slide bg-white p-12 lg:p-16 flex flex-col justify-center">
            <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-amber-600 mb-8">Our Unique Value Proposition</h2>
            <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-6">We are the only VR intervention that combines:</p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 grid-rows-2 gap-4">
                <div class="bg-amber-50 p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-amber-400">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-amber-800 mb-1">1. Clinical Oversight</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-700">A tool *for* therapists, not a replacement. Ensures safety and efficacy.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-amber-50 p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-amber-400">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-amber-800 mb-1">2. ADHD-Specific Protocols</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-700">Tools (like finger-tapping) designed for neurodivergent brains, not one-size-fits-all meditation.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-amber-50 p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-amber-400">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-amber-800 mb-1">3. Cultural Adaptation (Roadmap)</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-700">Future focus: Addressing demo limitations by adding regionalized environments (cultural appropriation) and humanized, multi-lingual voice guidance.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-amber-50 p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-amber-400">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-amber-800 mb-1">4. Evidence-Based & Scalable</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-700">Grounded in CBT, our model allows one therapist to effectively support many clients.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 11: The Roadmap & Ask -->
